This paper deals with the construction of a plane spanner, which is a geometric graph that approximates the complete graph. This topic is closely related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph algorithms (cs.DS). The algorithm described in the paper involves the use of data structures and optimization techniques, which are also relevant to the sub-categories of cs.DM (discrete mathematics) and cs.NA (numerical analysis). Finally, the paper presents experimental results that demonstrate the effectiveness of the algorithm, which could be of interest to researchers in the sub-category of cs.SI (social and information networks).
